  "rationale": "V5 improved the new field validation source but catastrophically forgot potato and rice behavior from the selected v3 model. Preserve the natural original-data distribution, bound the new source to a 3x sampling multiplier, and distill v3 predictions on every original-source sample while learning expert labels normally. Calibration cannot sharpen below temperature 1.0 because both earlier selected and v5 candidates were overconfident on held-out field data.",
  "test_disclosure": "The immutable test has been observed for earlier candidates, including v5. Only aggregate gate and source-level failure patterns informed this preservation recipe. No test image, label, logit, duplicate, or per-example failure enters training, checkpoint selection, calibration, or threshold selection. Independent field validation remains required.",
